mind
to
stay.
It
grows
late;
the
dew
falls
heavily.
You
and
Caroline
will
enjoy
each
other's
society,
I
doubt
not."
"I
promise
you,
then,
to
stay
with
Caroline,"
replied
Shirley.
"As
you
say,
we
shall
enjoy
each
other's
society.
We
will
not
be
separated
to
night.
Now,
rejoin
your
old
friend,
and
fear
nothing
for
