stood
listening
at
the
casement,
"Shirley,
I
hear
the
beck
in
the
Hollow."
Then
she
rang
the
bell,
asked
for
a
candle
and
some
bread
and
milk
Miss
Keeldar's
usual
supper
and
her
own.
Fanny,
when
she
brought
in
the
tray,
would
have
closed
the
windows
and
the
